<h2><big>Overview</big></h2>
<p>Duffel is a trip planning and bookmarking tool for travelers and non-travelers.</p>
<p>Why non-travelers? Because trip planning doesn't begin when you start researching hotels and things to do. It begins when you see a story featuring hip Paris caf√©s, an interesting article about a Greek temple built 4000 years ago, or when a friend recommends the best beach resort at Maui. Save those articles and ideas with just one click.</p>
<p>Duffel uses virtual corkboard that organizes and helps you visualize your travel itineraries.</p>
<p>When you're thinking about your vacation, you may want to dine out at a <strong>Zagat's top-rated restaurant</strong>, swim in a <strong>hidden beach</strong> that 
	your friends recommended, and rest your legs at <strong>Trip Advisor's most popular hotel</strong>.	
	Duffel is not only a place where you can collaboratively store, organize and archive all these 
	travel ideas and trips, but you can also use them to compile your own itineraries that go hand-in-hand with your
	favorite travel guidebook.
</p>  

